AWS Flow Logs:
==============

- Capture info about IP traffic going into the interfaces
- VPC Flow Logs
- Subnet Flow Logs
- ENI Flow Logs

- Helps to monitor and troubleshoot connectivity issues
- Flow logs data can go to S3/ CloudWatch logs
- Captures network info from AWS managed services such as ELB, RDS, ElasticCache, Redshift, Workspaces


- srcaddr, dstaddr help identify problematic IP
- scrport, dstport help identify problematic PORTS
- Action: success or failure
- Can be used for analytics on usage patterns or malicious behaviour
- Query VPC flow logs using Athena or CloudWatch Logs insights
